Package org.jtrim2.stream

Interface ElementConsumer<T>

Type Parameters:
T - the type of the element being processed
public interface ElementConsumer<T>
Defines an action processing element(s) of a stream of elements. The action is either context free or has an otherwise implied context. If you need to do something before or after processing the stream, consider using SeqConsumer instead.

Note that implementations of this interface

Thread safety

The thread-safety property of this interface are completely implementation dependent.

Synchronization transparency

Implementations of this interface are not required to be synchronization transparent.

    • processElement

      void processElement(T element) throws Exception
      Processes a single element of the underlying stream. This method is called for each elements of the stream exactly once (in the order defined by the stream, if any).
      Parameters:
      element - the element being processed. This argument may not be null.
      Throws:
      OperationCanceledException - thrown if cancellation of the stream processing was detected by this method call. Note that although this method does not accept a CancellationToken for the sake of simplicity, the context usually has one.
      Exception - thrown if there was a processing failure. This usually means that the whole processing of the stream is to be discontinued.
